Wishing you, our DECIEM family, a safe and Happy New Year! 🎊🎆

We’re all good. 🤗

After a year of ups and downs, we’ve partnered with positive news media company @goodgoodgoodco to celebrate all of the good things that have happened in 2021 to say goodbye to the old, and hello to the new.

Inside this issue, you will find uplifting stories, some happy stories about DECIEM, and exercises to help us all put our best foot forward in 2022. 

You can find a print copy of this newspaper in our stores, or access a digital version via the link in our bio. 

Happy reading. <3

latestIgtvVideos.title: Everything Is Chemicals (including “clean” beauty)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Over the last few months, our Scientific team has been sharing information to shed light on the subject of ingredient and product safety, in order to help us all better understand the chemistry of the world around us, and to continue our message of "Everything is Chemicals"--(including 'clean' beauty).

The message doesn't stop there - Humans are entirely made of chemicals, too, and so is everything around us: from the things we can see, to the many that we can’t, from the foods we can taste, to the flowers we can smell, the solids we can grab, and the gases we cannot. When we understand that everything is made of chemicals, we understand that it is illogical to fear them - and a gentler approach may be to learn about them, particularly through a scientific lens, by lending from the important work that scientists around the world are publishing every day. 

Our Scientific team has shared information about the misunderstood nature of silicones, the work that goes into deeming if a product is safe before it makes it to your shelf, why we want to rename 'filler ingredients' to 'inactive ingredients', and they have much more to share: about the recently notorious Benzene in SPFs and PFASs in colour cosmetics, parabens, why we love alcohols, and that if we could, we would give sulphates a really big hug.

To know more about our approach, please visit our #EIC highlight, look through the #everythingischemicals hashtag, and stay tuned - because the only way to not fear the unknown is to embrace it, and to learn more.

P.S., Our lab has been really busy. They have just been included in the very first brand-owned @spatenyc report, combining efforts from skin science to data science to provide insight into the rising concerns around skin sensitivity, inflammation, and ingredient safety. To read more, please visit our link in bio.

latestIgtvVideos.title: How To Reuse DECIEM Bottles
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Reusing DECIEM bottles is a great way to reduce waste, but thinking of creative ways to integrate DECIEM bottles into your everyday life can be challenging. 🤔 To make things a little bit easier, we've created a step-by-step video to guide you along your journey. 🌎 ❤️

🧴 STEP 1 - Select the bottle you'd like to reuse and consider how you'd like to give your bottle a new life.

🧴 STEP 2 - Clean your dropper bottle using soap 🧼 and water 💧; dropper bottles can also be boiled so that labels can be easily removed, and don't forget, make sure you clean the dropper as well. 

🧴 STEP 3 - Let's get creative! DECIEM bottles can be used to house hot sauce, hold flowers, make your own vanilla extract, or contain spices. Interested in learning how? Keep watching.👆

🧴 STEP 4 - We also have a recycling program called Terracycle to dispose of any bottles you don't want to reuse.  At this time, Terracycle is only available in Canada, USA, and UK, but we're working hard to expand the program further.

We'd love to hear👂from you. What are some ways you've reused DECIEM bottles?

latestIgtvVideos.title: Sustainability at DECIEM
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
DECIEM is not a sustainable beauty company and we recognize by nature of our business, we may never be fully sustainable. We are committed to improving all areas of our operations.

We’re continually assessing our impact on the planet and innovating to do better. DECIEM is working to give back to the Earth in five ways: through more responsible packaging, fighting climate change, better waste management, responsible sourcing and product lifecycle, and water conservation.

On Monday, our very own Jacquelyn Kankam, Director of Sustainability and Social Impact, joined Nicola Kilner, Co-Founder & CEO, on @wearedeciem to discuss all things sustainability, including the importance of companies respecting the earth, the current state of climate change, DECIEM's initiatives, and how our community can get involved. 🌏🌱

If you missed the live event, don't worry, we recorded it for you 🤗 (but be sure to follow @wearedeciem so you don't miss out on any future events). 

If you're interested in learning about DECIEM's initiatives in more depth we encourage you to visit https://deciem.com/nl/deciem-earth.html. ❤️

latestIgtvVideos.title: DECIEM’s Footprint
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Meet Jackie Kankam - our Director of Sustainability and Social Impact. Jackie and her incredible team here at DECIEM play a critical role in the implementation of strategies to minimize our carbon footprint. 
 
With her support, we’ve recently welcomed three beloved products from The Ordinary to our supersized set. This means you can get more of what you love at a better price and most importantly, help to reduce your footprint (and ours). If you love The Ordinary Alpha Arbutin 2% + HA, Salicylic Acid 2% Masque, Azelaic Acid Suspension 10%, “Buffet”, Hyaluronic Acid 2% + B5, Niacinamide 10% + Zinc 1%, Squalane Cleanser and/or Natural Moisturizing Factors + HA already, consider supersizing for a more human approach to beauty. 
 
It’s just one way to hug the earth a bit tighter 🤗🌍.
